  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing  Emergency WASH services  to conflict-affected population (newly displaced populations from Hawija and Shirqat ) in camps of Salah Al-Din governorate</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will provide expected IDPs with emergency water trucking to cover the lack of domestic water .Also, the project will support the collection and disposal of solid waste and solid amp sewerage waste management inside the camps. 
The project will provide emergency fuel to the generators of RO units in Al-Alam 3,4 camp to ensure the continuity of providing safe drinking water.
The project will distribute 380 garbage bins and 5000 garbage bags to help in collect the solid waste. 
In addition, the project will provide hygiene promotion through dissemination of key messages to the affected IDPs families in AlAlam 3,4 camp ,Tal Sebat Screening site and out of camp response in Areas around Hawija.

Inadequate water and sanitation services put women and children at particular risk of disease. Therefore Sorouh will activate the role of outreach teams from the IDPs families to address the limited knowledge in water consuming , hygiene awareness , environmental good practices and related messages for newly displaced people in Salah al-din .

The project will identify amp train 70 women and girls on the hygiene promotion and community mobilization, in order to establish 7 outreach teams, which will help to minimize the risk of dieses that can improve IDPs life. 35 local authorities, Mukhtars and host community leaders will be enrolled in community mobilization and hygiene promotion.

Also, 35 IDPs figures in AlAlam will be actively engaged in community engagement, community-focused initiatives including minimizing water consumption , good hygiene practices , awareness raising campaigns.

Arrangements will be done in coordination with the local authorities, CCCM, Mukhtars and selected IDPs figures in each location.
Total number of project direct beneficiaries reaches : 15,156 IDPs . 
The project shall last for 5 months starting from 1st of October, 2017 and ending in 28 Feb, 2018.</narrative>
  </description>
